verses.verse: A Song of the steps. To thee who dwellest in heaven, I have raised mine eyes.
Behold! as the eyes of servants are on the hands of their masters; as the eyes of a maid are on the hands of her mistress, so are our eyes on the Lord our God, till he be gracious to us.
Have mercy on us, Lord; have mercy on us; for we are exceedingly filled with contempt.
Our soul is filled exceedingly; we are the scoff of the prosperous and the contempt of the haughty.
